description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a motivated and enthusiastic administrator to join the Trust and provide Personal Assistant support to the Corporate Operations Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must have strong prioritisation and excellent organisational skills together with the ability to remain calm and collected in a busy dynamic environment. The post holder must be able to communicate effectively with a wide range of workforce groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual with proven experience working at a senior Personal Assistant level, preferably in the NHS and within an operations team. Experience of project management would also be advantageous. Candidates must be able to demonstrate advanced secretarial skills, both written and verbal and be able to liaise confidently with internal and external stakeholders, be competent with IT skills, in particular Excel, Word, Emails and electronic diary management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time post working 37.5 hours per week Monday to Friday. Hours will be flexible according to the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caroline Vinnicombe, Business Manager, Chief Executive Office caroline.vinnicombe@nhs.net or 01872 252902&lt;/p&gt;
